For a smile, they can share the night

Up and down the boulevard

snippet.title: State of Play | September 24, 2025 [English]
snippet.description:
Tune in live this Wednesday for more than 35 minutes of reveals and news from developers around the world. We’ll share new looks at anticipated third-party and indie titles, plus updates from some of our teams at PlayStation Studios - including an extended look at Saros, Housemarque’s mysterious new title arriving next year. Look forward to nearly five minutes of gameplay captured on PS5.

The next State of Play begins September 24 at 2pm PT / 5pm ET / 11pm CEST | September 25 at 6am JST on YouTube and Twitch, and will be broadcast in English with Japanese subtitles also available. See you then!

Regarding co-streaming and video-on-demand (VOD)

Please note that this broadcast may include copyrighted content (e.g. licensed music) that PlayStation does not control. We welcome and celebrate our amazing co-streamers and creators, but licensing agreements outside our control could interfere with co-streams or VOD archives of this broadcast. If you’re planning to save this broadcast as a VOD to create recap videos, or to repost clips or segments from the show, we advise omitting any copyrighted music.

snippet.title: Wicked: For Good | Final Trailer
snippet.description:
The final #WickedForGood trailer is here ✨ Watch now.

Pre-order Wicked: For Good - The Soundtrack 💚🩷 available November 21st at https://wickedthesoundtrack.lnk.to/forgood
-----
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@wickedmovie
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/wickedmovie
X: https://twitter.com/wickedmovie
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/wickedmovie
Official Site: https://wickedmovie.com

And now whatever way our stories end, I know you have rewritten mine by being my friend …

Last year’s global cinematic cultural sensation, which became the most successful Broadway film adaptation of all time, now reaches its epic, electrifying, emotional conclusion in Wicked: For Good. 

Directed once again by award-winning director Jon M. Chu and starring the spectacular returning cast, led by Academy Award® nominated superstars Cynthia Erivo and Ariana Grande, the final chapter of the untold story of the witches of Oz begins with Elphaba and Glinda estranged and living with the consequences of their choices. 

Elphaba (Cynthia Erivo), now demonized as The Wicked Witch of the West, lives in exile, hidden within the Ozian forest while continuing her fight for the freedom of Oz’s silenced Animals and desperately trying to expose the truth she knows about The Wizard (Jeff Goldblum).  

Glinda, meanwhile, has become the glamorous symbol of Goodness for all of Oz, living at the palace in Emerald City and reveling in the perks of fame and popularity. Under the instruction of Madame Morrible (Oscar® winner Michelle Yeoh), Glinda is deployed to serve as an effervescent comfort to Oz, reassuring the masses that all is well under the rule of The Wizard.  

As Glinda’s stardom expands and she prepares to marry Prince Fiyero (Olivier award winner and Emmy and SAG nominee Jonathan Bailey) in a spectacular Ozian wedding, she is haunted by her separation from Elphaba. She attempts to broker a conciliation between Elphaba and The Wizard, but those efforts will fail, driving Elphaba and Glinda only further apart. The aftershocks will transform Boq (Tony nominee Ethan Slater) and Fiyero forever, and threaten the safety of Elphaba’s sister, Nessarose (Marissa Bode), when a girl from Kansas comes crashing into all their lives. 

As an angry mob rises against the Wicked Witch, Glinda and Elphaba will need to come together one final time. With their singular friendship now the fulcrum of their futures, they will need to truly see each other, with honesty and empathy, if they are to change themselves, and all of Oz, for good. 

Wicked: For Good also stars Emmy nominee Bowen Yang and Bronwyn James as Glinda’s fawning assistants, Pfannee and ShenShen and BAFTA and Grammy nominee Sharon D. Clarke (Caroline, or Change) as the voice of Elphaba’s childhood nanny, Dulcibear. 

The film is produced by returning Tony and Emmy winning powerhouse Marc Platt p.g.a. and by multiple Tony winner David Stone. The executive producers are Stephen Schwartz, David Nicksay, Jared LeBoff, Winnie Holzman and Dana Fox. The first film, Wicked, released in November 2024, earned 10 Academy Award® nominations, including Best Picture, and won the Oscars® for Costume Design and Production Design. To date, the film has grossed $750 million worldwide. 

Wicked: For Good is based on the generation-defining musical stage play with music and lyrics by legendary Grammy and Oscar® winning composer and lyricist Stephen Schwartz and book by Winnie Holzman, from the bestselling novel by Gregory Maguire. The screenplay is by Winnie Holzman and Winnie Holzman & Dana Fox. The film score is by John Powell & Stephen Schwartz, with music and lyrics by Stephen Schwartz.

snippet.description:
#Netflix #Onepiece #Onepiece2

🎥 Attention viewers! (ITS FAN MADE)
The Straw Hats are back! Netflix’s One Piece Live Action Season 2 brings Luffy, Zoro, Nami, Usopp, and Sanji deeper into the Grand Line as epic new adventures unfold. With Iñaki Godoy returning as Monkey D. Luffy and Mackenyu as Zoro, fans will meet new allies like Chopper and Vivi, face powerful enemies like Smoker, Miss All Sunday, and more, while the Going Merry sails into uncharted waters. Packed with action, adaptation from Oda’s legendary manga, and stunning live-action visuals, this season promises even bigger battles, emotional moments, and surprises. The adventure continues in 2026 on Netflix—don’t miss it!

The inspiration behind this video:
The epic One Piece Live Action Season 2 trailer has arrived on Netflix, bringing fans back Into the Grand Line with the Straw Hats! Starring Iñaki Godoy as Luffy, Mackenyu as Zoro, and the crew aboard the Going Merry, this Epic Adventure introduces Chopper, Vivi, Miss Wednesday, Miss All Sunday, and even teases the appearance of Smoker and Laboon. Based on Oda’s Manga, this Adaptation of the beloved Anime continues to expand the journey of friendship, dreams, and Pirates sailing toward destiny.

From the One Piece Season 2 trailer Netflix to reactions across the community, fans can catch every detail in this One Piece Season 2 official trailer, One Piece Season 2 sneak peek, and behind-the-scenes hype. With exciting breakdowns by IGN, IGN TV trailer, Teaser PRO, FilmSpot Trailer, MovieGasm, KinoCheck, and EmergencyAwesome, the One Piece Season 2 reaction wave is here. snippet.title: PÖBEL MC - WIND (beat by Tombs Beats)
snippet.description:
Vielen fühlen sich einsam, auch weil diese Welt uns einsam macht, teilweise uns einsam will und gerade Männer haben nach wie vor große Schwierigkeiten ihre Gefühle angemessen zu kommunizieren und auszuleben. Lasst euch nicht allein, ihr seid nicht allein, lebt mit den Menschen und euren Unterschieden, daher kommt auch das Wort Mitmenschlichkeit und nur so kann eine mitmenschliche Welt gestaltet werden, die durch den zunehmenden, aber noch aufhaltbaren, Aufstieg des Faschismus im Grundlegendsten bedroht ist. Das Innere, Emotionale ist vom Äußeren, Sachlichen nicht zu trennen und so müssen wir auf beiden Ebenen arbeiten. Die Bunker in uns bedingen die Bunker um uns und dieser Sinnlosigkeit können wir nur gemeinsam begegnen.

Die Bunker in uns bedingen die Bunker um uns und dieser Sinnlosigkeit können wir nur gemeinsam begegnen.
